de.learnlib.filters.reuse.tree

Class ReuseNode<S,I,O>

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.learnlib.filters.reuse.tree.ReuseNode<S,I,O>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - system state class
    I - input symbol class
    O - output symbol class

    public class ReuseNode<S,I,O>
extends Object
    A ReuseNode is a vertex in the ReuseTree that contains (a possible empty) set of outgoing ReuseEdges. Each ReuseNode may contain a system state holding relevant informations (e.g. database identifiers or an object) that belongs to the system state that 'represents' the system state after executing a membership query.
    Author:
    Oliver Bauer
